{"title_page": "Arani, Tiruvannamalai District", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Arani\n| native_name                     = Silk City\n| native_name_lang                = Tamil\n| other_name                      = \u0b86\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\n| settlement_type                 = Select Grade Municipality\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_caption                   = Arani Silk sarees,  Anna University,  Arani Road Railway Station,  Arani Old Bus stand,  Jagir Palace,   French Fort\n| image_map                       = \n| nickname                        = Silk & Rice City\n| pushpin_map                     = India Tamil Nadu#India\n| pushpin_label_position          = left\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in [[Tamil Nadu]]##Location in India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|12.6751077|N|79.2843245|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1               = State\n| subdivision_type2               = District\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Tamilnadu]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Tiruvannamalai district|Tiruvannamalai]]\n| subdivision_type3               = Zone\n| subdivision_name3               = Tondai Region\n| subdivision_type4               = \n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date                = \n| founder                         = \n| named_for                       = Silk & Rice\n| leader_title                    = Lok Sabha constituency\n| leader_name                     = [[Arani (Lok Sabha constituency)]]\n| leader_title1                   = Member of Lok Sabha constituency\n| leader_name1                    = Mr. M.k Vishnu Prasad\n| leader_title2                   = Member of Legislative Assembly\n| leader_name2                    = Mr. Sevoor. Ramachandran\n| leader_title3                   = District Collector\n| leader_name3                    = Mr.Kandhasamy IAS\n| leader_title4                   = Municipal Leader\n| leader_name4                    = Ashoke kumar\n| unit_pref                       = \n| area_footnotes                  = <ref name=census>{{cite web|title=District Census Handbook : Tiruvannamalai|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/3305_PART_B_DCHB_TIRUVANNAMALAI.pdf|website=Census of India|accessdate=21 June 2017|page=30|format=PDF}}</ref>\n| area_rank                       = 2nd in the District\n| area_total_km2                  = 13.64\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = 171\n| population_total                = 92375\n| population_metro                = 119574\n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| population_rank                 = 30\n| population_density_km2          = \n| population_demonym              = \n| demographics_type1              = Language\n| demographics1_title1            = Official Language\n| demographics1_info1             = Tamil\n| timezone1                       = Indian tuning time\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = Postal code\n| postal_code                     = 632301, 632314, 632316 , 632317, 632318 , 632326\n| area_code_type                  = Phone numbers in India\n| area_code                       = 04173\n| registration_plate              = TN 97\n| website                         = {{URL|www.Arani.tn.nic.in|Arani Municipality}}\n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = \n}}\n\n'''Arani''' otherwise spelled '''Arni''', also '''Periya Arani''' is a town and a [[municipality]] in [[Tiruvanamalai district]] in the state of [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]. The name comes from the word A''ranyam'' which means a place surrounded by forest. Arani is known for its rich history - a Fort and few palaces, ancient Hindu temples and Jain centres stand today as a testimony.\n\nAs of 2011, the municipality boundary of the town had a population of 63,671, the extended town population is 92,375 and it is the 2nd largest town in the district after [[Tiruvannamalai]]. A revenue division of the district is formed which is headquartered by Arani.\n\nArani is the second largest city in the Tiruvannamalai district. Arani is the name of silk and pony varieties next to [[Kanchipuram]]. Arani is also known for its silk sarees. It is also known as the '''Arani Silk City'''. Arani is one of the highest income earning town in [[Tiruvannamalai district]]. Arani is the 30th largest city in Tamil Nadu with the most populous cities\n\n==Arani Municipality History==\n\n[[Arani]] was constituted as a third grade municipality in the year 1951. As per G.O. No. 564, date: 02.04.1951, classified as Second Grade Municipality. The population of the town was then 24567. The entire area of Arani Revenue village was included within the jurisdiction of the municipality.   At 2007 from 9.5.1983 onwards as per G.O. No. 851, classified as first grade municipality. The Population of the town was then 63741. At present From 2008 on words as per G.O No- 1067, Classified as Selection Grade Municipality. The Population of the town was then 92375 <ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20080409030902/http://municipality.tn.gov.in/arni/abs_Municipality.htm  Arani Municipality population]</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nArni is located at {{Coord|12.67|N|79.28|E|}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/25/Arani.html|title= Falling Rain Genomics \u2013 Arani}}</ref> on the banks of the [[Kamandala River|Kamandala Naaga]] river. It has an average elevation of {{convert|151|m|ft}}.\n\n==Transport==\n===Road facilities===\nArni is well connected to major cities by road and road.The city of Arni is connected by various well-paved roads,\n\n* State Highways - 4 [[Arcot]] - Arni - [[Chetpet]] - [[Gingee]] - [[Villupuram]] Road\n* State Highway 132 [[Bangalore]] - [[Vellore]] - Arni Road\n* State Highway - 505 & 770 & 116 & 58 & 120 [[Tambaram]] - [[Kanchipuram]] -[[Cheyyar]] - Arni Road\n* District Road - 40 Arni - [[Devikapuram]] - [[Avalurpet]] Road\n* District Road - 751 Arni - [[Sandhavasal|Sandavasal]] - [[Padaiveedu|Padavedu]] Road\n* District Road - Arni - [[Arcot, Vellore|Valaipandal]] - [[Cheyyar]] Road\n* State Highway - 43 & 5 & 32 Arni - [[Vandavasi]] - [[Tindivanam]] - [[Puducherry]] Road\n* State Highway - 41 & 38 & 6A & 18 Arni - [[Thiruvannamalai]] - [[Salem, Tamil Nadu|Salem]] and [[Trichy]] Road\n* State Highway - NH133 Arni - [[Polur|Etiwadi]] - [[Polur]] - [[Chengam]] Road\n\nA bypass of [[Chennai]] (Arcot) Road, [[Chennai]] Road and [[Cuddalore]] Road is being completed.\n\n===Bus Transport===\n\nIt is {{cvt|126|km}} from Chennai, {{convert|38|km|0}} from [[Vellore]] and {{convert|60|km|0}} from [[Tiruvannamalai]]. There are two bus stands in the town and a [[TNSTC]] operates a daily service to important south Tamilnadu cities. '''''Arani''''' to '''''Chennai''''' has an every 10 minutes once a bus at 02:15AM to 10:45PM. The major inter-city bus routes to towns has predominant bus services to [[Vellore]], [[Tiruvannamalai]], [[Kanchipuram]] and [[Villupuram]], [[Bangalore]], [[Salem, Tamil Nadu|salem]], [[Coimbatore]], [[Tirupur]], [[Erode]], [[Trichy]], [[Thanjavur]], [[Tiruvallur]], [[Thiruttani|Tirutani]], [[Tirupati|Tirupathi]], [[Puduchery]], [[Thoothukudi]], [[Nagercoil|Nagarkoil]], [[Chidambaram]], [[Tindivanam]], [[Nagapattinam]], [[Madurai]] and [[Cuddalore]]. The [[State Express Transport Corporation (Tamil Nadu)|SETC]] & [[Tamil Nadu State Transport Corporation|TNSTC]] operates long distance buses routes to the important cities.\n\nMany buses are running powered from the Arani and other than. Some of them are:\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|-\n!Bus Number \n!Place of Departure\n! Destination\n! Route \n|-\n|202\n|ARANI\n|[[Chennai|CHENNAI]]\n|[[Arcot, Vellore|ARCOT]]\n|-\n|210\n|[[Tiruvannamalai|TIRUVANNAMALAI]]\n|[[Chennai|CHENNAI]]\n|[[Kalasapakkam|KALASAPAKKAM]], [[Polur|POLUR]], ARANI, [[Arcot, Vellore|ARCOT]], [[Poonamallee|POONAMALLEE]]\n|-\n|204 UD\n|[[Polur|POLUR]]\n|[[Chennai|CHENNAI]]\n|[[Kalambur|KALAMBUR]], ARANI, [[Arcot, Vellore|ARCOT]], [[Poonamallee|POONAMALLEE]]\n|-\n|423\n|[[Tiruvannamalai|TIRUVANNAMALAI]]\n|[[Chennai|CHENNAI]]\n|[[Kalasapakkam|KALASAPAKKAM]], [[Polur|POLUR]], ARANI, [[Cheyyar|CHEYYAR]], [[Kanchipuram|KANCHIPURAM]], [[Poonamallee|POONAMALLEE]]\n|-\n|135\n|ARANI\n|[[Kanchipuram|KANCHIPURAM]]\n|[[Kalavai|KALAVAI]], [[Vembakkam|VEMBAKKAM]]\n|-\n|235\n|[[Tiruvannamalai|TIRUVANNAMALAI]]\n|[[Kanchipuram|KANCHIPURAM]]\n|[[Kalasapakkam|KALASAPAKKAM]], [[Polur|POLUR]], ARANI, [[Cheyyar|CHEYYAR]]\n|-\n|438\n|[[Kanchipuram|KANCHIPURAM]]\n|[[SALEM]]\n|[[Cheyyar|CHEYYAR]], ARANI, [[Polur|POLUR]], [[Tiruvannamalai|TIRUVANAMALAI]], [[Harur|HARUR]]\n|-\n|502\n|[[Tiruvallur|TIRUVALLUR]]\n|ARANI\n|[[Kanchipuram|KANCHIPURAM]], [[Arcot, Vellore|ARCOT]]\n|-\n|477\n|ARANI\n|[[BANGALORE]]\n|[[Polur|POLUR]], [[Tiruvannamalai|TIRUVANAMALAI]], [[Krishnagiri|KRISHNAGIRI]], [[Hosur|HOSUR]]\n|-\n|444\n|ARANI\n|[[BANGALORE]]\n|[[Vellore|VELLORE]], [[Krishnagiri|KRISHNAGIRI]]\n|-\n|216\n|[[Vellore|VELLORE]]\n|[[Viluppuram|VILLUPURAM]]\n|ARANI, [[Chettupattu|CHETTUPATTU]], [[Gingee|GINGEE]]\n|-\n|217\n|ARANI\n|[[Vellore|VELLORE]]\n|[[Kannamangalam, Malappuram|KANNAMANGALAM]], [[Kaniyambadi block|KANIYAMBADI]], [[Adukkamparai|ADUKKAMBARAI]]\n|-\n|434\n|ARANI\n|[[Coimbatore|COIMBATORE]]\n|[[Polur|POLUR]], [[Tiruvannamalai|TIRUVANNAMALAI]], [[Harur|HARUR]], [[SALEM]]\n|-\n|435\n|ARANI\n|[[Tiruppur|TIRUPUR]]\n|[[Polur|POLUR]], [[Tiruvannamalai|TIRUVANNAMALAI]], [[Harur|HARUR]], [[SALEM]]\n|-\n|432\n|ARANI\n|[[Erode|ERODE]]\n|[[Polur|POLUR]], [[Tiruvannamalai|TIRUVANNAMALAI]], [[Harur|HARUR]], [[SALEM]]\n|-\n|666\n|[[Kanchipuram|KANCHIPURAM]]\n|[[Tiruchirappalli|TRICHY]]\n|[[Cheyyar|CHEYYAR]], ARANI, [[Polur|POLUR]], [[Tiruvannamalai|TIRUVANNAMALAI]], [[Perambalur|PERAMBALUR]]\n|-\n|242\n|[[Chengam|CHENGAM]]\n|[[Chennai|CHENNAI]]\n|[[Polur|POLUR]], ARANI, [[Cheyyar|CHEYYAR]], [[Kanchipuram|KANCHIPURAM]], [[Poonamallee|POONAMALLEE]]\n|-\n|204\n|[[Vellore|VELLORE]]\n|[[Puducherry|PUDUCHERRY]]\n|ARANI, [[Vandavasi|VANDAVASI]], [[Tindivanam|TINDIVANAM]],\n|-\n|163\n|[[Tiruvannamalai|TIRUVANNAMALAI]]\n|[[Thiruttani|TIRUTANI]]\n|[[Polur|POLUR]], ARANI, [[Arcot, Vellore|ARCOT]]\n|-\n|279\n|ARANI\n|[[Tambaram|TAMBARAM]]\n|[[Cheyyar|CHEYYAR]], [[Kanchipuram|KANCHIPURAM]], [[Padappai|PADAPPAI]]\n|-\n|234\n|ARANI\n|[[T. Nagar|T.NAGAR]]\n|[[Arcot, Vellore|ARCOT]], [[Poonamallee|POONAMALLEE]], [[Guindy|GUINDY]], [[Saidapet|SAIDAPET]]\n|-\n| UD (SETC)\n|[[Vellore|VELLORE]]\n|[[Thoothukudi|THOOTHUKUDI]]\n|ARANI, [[Viluppuram|VILLUPURAM]], [[Tiruchirappalli|TRICHY]]\n|-\n| UD (SETC)\n|[[Vellore|VELLORE]]\n|[[Thanjavur|THANJAVUR]]\n|ARANI, [[Viluppuram|VILLUPURAM]]\n|-\n|307\n|[[Arani|ARANI]]\n|[[Tiruchirappalli|TRICHY]]\n| ARANI, [[Polur|POLUR]], [[Tiruvannamalai|TIRUVANNAMALAI]], [[Perambalur|PERAMBALUR]]\n|-\n|665\n|[[Vellore|VELLORE]]\n|[[Pudukkottai|PUDHUKOTTAI]]\n|ARANI, [[Viluppuram|VILLUPURAM]]\n|-\n| UD\n|[[Vellore|VELLORE]]\n|[[Mayiladuthurai|MAYILADUTHURAI]]\n|ARANI,[[Viluppuram|VILLUPURAM]]\n|-\n|}\n\n===Train Transport===\n\nThe Tindivanam route from the city is planned by the central government to connect trains via Arani. The railway station has been shifted to Kalambur on the Arani - Thiruvannamalai road. The railway station is the Arani railway station. It is located on the Arani - Thiruvannamalai road about {{cvt|10|km}} away. However, it is the nearest railway station to the business town of Arani, {{cvt|10|km}} away. The station is the third largest railway station in the district, apart from the Thiruvannamalai town and the Arani Railway Junction station. Opened in 1889 for public use. The railway station is well connected to cities like Bangalore, Svandpur, Vellore - Katpadi, Kolkata Howrah, Tirupati, Cuddalore, Pondicherry, Mannargudi, Mayavaram, Kumbakonam, Trichy, Dindigul, Madurai, Chennai Central, Arakkonam and Tiruvallur.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Train Name !! Train Number !! Place of Departure!! Train Route !! Place of Destination\n|-\n| [[Tirupati|Tirupathi]]-[[Villupuram]] passenger train || 56885 || [[Tirupati|Tirupathi]]|| [[Chittore]], [[Katpadi]], [[Vellore]], [[Kannamangalam, Malappuram|Kannamangalam]], Arani, [[polur]], [[Tiruvannamalai]], [[Tirukoilur|Tirukovilur]]||[[Villupuram]]\n|-\n| [[Villupuram]] [[Katpadi]] passengers || 56886 || [[Villupuram]] || [[Vellore]], [[Kannamangalam, Malappuram|Kannamangalam]], Arani, [[polur]], [[Tiruvannamalai]], [[Tirukoilur|Tirukovilur]]||[[Katpadi]]\n|-\n| [[Katpadi]] [[Villupuram]] passengers || 56881 || [[Katpadi]] || [[Katpadi]], [[Vellore]], [[Kannamangalam, Malappuram|Kannamangalam]], Arani, [[polur]], [[Tiruvannamalai]], [[Tirukoilur|Tirukovilur]]||[[Villupuram]]\n|-\n| [[Villupuram]]-[[Tirupati|Tirupathi]] || 56882 || [[Villupuram]] || [[Katpadi]], [[Vellore]], [[Kannamangalam, Malappuram|Kannamangalam]], Arani, [[polur]], [[Tiruvannamalai]], [[Tirukoilur|Tirukovilur]]||[[Tirupati|Tirupathi]]\n|-\n| [[Katpadi]]-[[Villupuram]]|| 56883 || [[Katpadi]] || [[Katpadi]], [[Vellore]], [[Kannamangalam, Malappuram|Kannamangalam]], Arani, [[polur]], [[Tiruvannamalai]], [[Tirukoilur|Tirukovilur]]||[[Villupuram]]\n|-\n| [[Katpadi]]-[[Villupuram]] || 56884 || [[Katpadi]] || [[Katpadi]], [[Vellore]], [[Kannamangalam, Malappuram|Kannamangalam]], Arani, [[polur]], [[Tiruvannamalai]], [[Tirukoilur|Tirukovilur]]||[[Villupuram]]\n|-\n| Brulia SF Express|| 22606|| [[Villupuram]] || [[Katpadi]], [[Vellore]], [[Kannamangalam, Malappuram|Kannamangalam]], Arani, [[polur]], [[Tiruvannamalai]], [[Tirukoilur|Tirukovilur]]|| Brulia\n|-\n|Bamani SF Express || 17407 || [[Tirupati|Tirupathi]] || || [[Mannargudi]]\n|-\n| Chalukya Express || 11005 || Mumbai Dadhar || [[Villupur